[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = HiddenMarkovModels","category":"page"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for HiddenMarkovModels.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [HiddenMarkovModels]","category":"page"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.HiddenMarkovModels","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.HiddenMarkovModels","text":"HiddenMarkovModels\n\nA Julia package for HMM modeling, simulation, inference and learning.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.AbstractHMM","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.AbstractHMM","text":"AbstractHMM\n\nShortcut for AbstractHiddenMarkovModel.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.AbstractHiddenMarkovModel","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.AbstractHiddenMarkovModel","text":"AbstractHiddenMarkovModel\n\nInterface for Hidden Markov Models with arbitrary emissions.\n\nRequired methods\n\nnb_states(hmm, θ)\ninitial_distribution(hmm, θ)\ntransition_matrix(hmm, θ)\nemission_distribution(hmm, i, θ)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Base.rand-Tuple{Random.AbstractRNG, AbstractHiddenMarkovModel, Any, Integer}","page":"Home","title":"Base.rand","text":"rand(rng, hmm, T, θ)\nrand(hmm, T, θ)\n\nSimulate hmm for T time steps and return a named tuple (state_seq, obs_seq).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.backward!-Tuple{Matrix, Matrix, Vector, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.backward!","text":"backward!(β, bβ, A, B)\n\nPerform a backward pass by mutating β and bβ (after forward pass).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.baum_welch!-Tuple{HiddenMarkovModel, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.baum_welch!","text":"baum_welch(hmm::HMM, obs_seqs; max_iterations, tol)\n\nApply the Baum-Welch algorithm on multiple observation sequences, starting from an initial estimate hmm.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.emission_distribution","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.emission_distribution","text":"emission_distribution(hmm, θ, i)\n\nReturn the emission distribution in state i for hmm with parameters θ.\n\nThe result must satisfy the DensityInterface.jl specification.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.emission_distributions-Tuple{AbstractHiddenMarkovModel, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.emission_distributions","text":"emission_distributions(hmm, θ)\n\nReturn the vector of emission distributions for hmm with parameters θ.\n\nEach element of the result result must satisfy the DensityInterface.jl specification.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.fit_mle_from_multiple_sequences-Union{Tuple{D}, Tuple{Type{D}, Any, Any}} where D","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.fit_mle_from_multiple_sequences","text":"fit_mle_from_multiple_sequences(::Type{D}, xs, ws)\n\nFit a distribution of type D based on multiple sequences of observations xs associated with multiple sequences of weights ws.\n\nMust accept arbitrary iterables for xs and ws.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.fit_mle_from_single_sequence-Union{Tuple{D}, Tuple{Type{D}, AbstractVector, AbstractVector}} where D","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.fit_mle_from_single_sequence","text":"fit_mle_from_single_sequence(::Type{D}, x, w)\n\nFit a distribution of type D based on a single sequence of observations x associated with a single sequence of weights w.\n\nDefaults to Distributions.fit_mle, with a special case for vectors of vectors (because Distributions.fit_mle accepts matrices instead). Users are free to override this default for concrete distributions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.forward!-Tuple{Matrix, Vector, Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.forward!","text":"forward!(α, c, p, A, B)\n\nPerform a forward pass by mutating α and c.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.forward_backward!-Tuple{Matrix, Vector, Matrix, Matrix, Matrix, Array{<:Any, 3}, Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.forward_backward!","text":"forward_backward!(α, c, β, bβ, γ, ξ, p, A, B)\n\nApply the full forward-backward algorithm by mutating α, c, β, bβ, γ and ξ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.initial_distribution","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.initial_distribution","text":"initial_distribution(hmm, θ)\n\nReturn the vector of initial state probabilities for hmm with parameters θ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.is_prob_vec-Tuple{AbstractVector}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.is_prob_vec","text":"is_prob_vec(p; atol)\n\nCheck if p is a probability distribution vector.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.is_square-Tuple{AbstractMatrix}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.is_square","text":"is_square(A)\n\nCheck if A is a square matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.is_trans_mat-Tuple{AbstractMatrix}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.is_trans_mat","text":"is_trans_mat(A; atol)\n\nCheck if A is a transition matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.marginals!-Tuple{Matrix, Array, Matrix, Matrix, Matrix, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.marginals!","text":"marginals!(γ, ξ, α, β, bβ, A)\n\nCompute state and transition marginals by mutating γ and ξ (after backward pass).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.nb_states","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.nb_states","text":"nb_states(hmm, θ)\n\nReturn the number of states of hmm with parameters θ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.rand_prob_vec-Tuple{Random.AbstractRNG, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.rand_prob_vec","text":"rand_prob_vec(rng, N)\nrand_prob_vec(N)\n\nGenerate a random probability distribution vector of length N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.rand_trans_mat-Tuple{Random.AbstractRNG, Any}","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.rand_trans_mat","text":"rand_trans_mat(rng, N)\nrand_trans_mat(N)\n\nGenerate a random transition matrix of size N × N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HiddenMarkovModels.transition_matrix","page":"Home","title":"HiddenMarkovModels.transition_matrix","text":"transition_matrix(hmm, θ)\n\nReturn the matrix of state transition probabilities for hmm with parameters θ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
